            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002326",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-769d3732d4c38307-4b6aff twpub-769d3732d4c38307-39c75b twpub-769d3732d4c38307-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p class=\"footnote\"><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000000154\">[16]</$link><br>\n[ Doors fastened to all intents and purposes as here described may be seen in the older houses at Trapani. There is a slot on the outer side of the door by means of which a person who has left the room can shoot the bolt. My bedroom at the Albergo Centrale was fastened in this way.]</p></div></div>"
        },
