            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-769d3732d4c38307-4b6aff twpub-769d3732d4c38307-39c75b twpub-769d3732d4c38307-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002342": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002342",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-769d3732d4c38307-4b6aff twpub-769d3732d4c38307-39c75b twpub-769d3732d4c38307-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p class=\"footnote\"><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000000185\">[20]</$link><br>\n[ cf. “Il.” ii. 76. ἦ τοι ὄ γ’ ὦς εὶπὼν κατ’ ἄρ’ ἔζετο τοῖσι δ’ ἀνέστη<br>\nΝέστωρ, ὄς ῥα.......................................<br>\nὄ σφιν ἐὺ φρονέων ἀγορήσατο καὶ μετέειπεν.<br>\nThe Odyssean passage runs—<br>\n“ἦ τοι ὄ γ’ ὦς εὶπὼν κατ’ ἄρ’ ἔζετο τοῖσι δ’ ἀνέστη<br>\nΜεντορ ὄς ῥ’.......................................<br>\nὄ σφιν ἐὺ φρονέων ἀγορήσατο καὶ μετέειπεν.<br>\nIs it possible not to suspect that the name Mentor was coined upon that of Nestor?]</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002343": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002343",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-769d3732d4c38307-4b6aff twpub-769d3732d4c38307-39c75b twpub-769d3732d4c38307-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
