        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002760": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002760",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-769d3732d4c38307-4b6aff twpub-769d3732d4c38307-39c75b twpub-769d3732d4c38307-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p><a></a></p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002761": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002761",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-769d3732d4c38307-4b6aff twpub-769d3732d4c38307-39c75b twpub-769d3732d4c38307-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002762": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002762",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-769d3732d4c38307-4b6aff twpub-769d3732d4c38307-39c75b twpub-769d3732d4c38307-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p class=\"footnote\"><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000001234\">[122]</$link><br>\n[ I take the following from The Authoress of the Odyssey, p. 167. “It is clear from the text that there were two [caves] not one, but some one has enclosed in brackets the two lines in which the second cave is mentioned, I presume because he found himself puzzled by having a second cave sprung upon him when up to this point he had only been told of one.</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002763": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002763",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-769d3732d4c38307-4b6aff twpub-769d3732d4c38307-39c75b twpub-769d3732d4c38307-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002764": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002764",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-769d3732d4c38307-4b6aff twpub-769d3732d4c38307-39c75b twpub-769d3732d4c38307-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\"><p class=\"footnote\">“I venture to think that if he had known the ground he would not have been puzzled, for there are two caves, distant about 80 or 100 yards from one another.” The cave in which Ulysses hid his treasure is, as I have already said, identifiable with singular completeness. The other cave presents no special features, neither in the poem nor in nature.]</p></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002765": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/769d3732d4c38307/text/000002765",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-769d3732d4c38307-4b6aff twpub-769d3732d4c38307-39c75b twpub-769d3732d4c38307-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"chapter\">\n</div></div>"
        },
